                                                                                            <p class="word-copy-lh-mb"><strong>Keith Garebian</strong> of Canada has published a dozen poetry collections as well as numerous nonfiction books, including <em>William Hutt: Soldier Actor</em> and <em>The Making of </em>Cabaret (Oxford University Press). His fifty-year career has been honored by an anthology, <em>A Disciplined Passion: Essays on the Works of Keith Garebian</em>.</p>
